msContents.summary: Commentary on the Talkhīṣ aʻmāl al-ḥisāb, a treatise on mathematical operations by Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad Ibn al-Bannāʼ, with particular focus on calculations involving fractions and square roots. According to the notes of Mahdi Abdeljaouad and Jeffrey Oaks, the manuscript includes excerpts from 3 other treatises: Rafʻ al-ḥijāb ʻan wujūh aʻmāl al-ḥisāb (his own commentary on the Talkhīṣ); Maqālāt fī ʻilm al-ḥisāb; and Kitāb al-jabr wa-al-muqābalah (a treatise on algebra). 5 computational tables (f. 27r, 34v, 35r, 46v, 49v). Includes corrections of text and calculations.

supportDesc.extent: 96 leaves : 210 x 140 (177 x 115) mm. bound to 212 x 155 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 96; [1-96]; modern foliation in pencil, lower left recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribi script in brown ink, pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrications in red including citations and numbers; colophon in red ink.

binding.p: Later red leather with flap (Type II), tooled central mandorla and double frame. Spines repaired.

origin.p: Written in Granada, completed 11 Sha'ban A.H. 849 (November 1445) by Ibrāhīm Ibn al-Ḥusn (f. 96r).
